<headA><14-point>figure</14-point></headA>
<par>The figure group-tag is used for graphic figures.</par>
<par></par>

<headB>Attributes</headB>
<list><?Pub Lcl MarkerStyle="none"><bold>margin</bold>  Controls the justification of the figure in the current flowing text area. The values are<list><?Pub Lcl MarkerStyle="bulleted">
<item><sans-serif>left</sans-serif>   Left justified</item>
<item><sans-serif>center</sans-serif>   Centered</item>
<item><sans-serif>right</sans-serif>   Right justified</item></list></list>

<list><?Pub Lcl MarkerStyle="none"><bold>l-r</bold>  Horizontal indentation of the elements contained by figure. Depending on the attribute value, the element is indented from the flowing text's left margin.
<list><?Pub Lcl MarkerStyle="bulleted">
<item><sans-serif>column</sans-serif>   1.8 inches indentation</item>
<item><sans-serif>half-indent</sans-serif>   0.9 inches indentation</item>
<item><sans-serif>leftmargin</sans-serif>   0.05 inches indentation</item>
</list></list>

<list><?Pub Lcl MarkerStyle="none"><bold>id</bold>  An id is used to give the particular tag a unique identification to be used for references. Insert a unique name as id and create the actual cross reference by using the xref tag.</list>
